title: TC001-Successful Authentication via Email OTP
description: Verify that users can log in successfully using their email address with correct OTP input.
code:
import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Click the Login button to navigate to the login form.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div/div/div/div[2]/div/div/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Click on the Email tab to switch to email login form.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div/button[2]').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input the registered email address 'test' and click Send Verification Code.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[2]/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('test')
        

        # Input the correct OTP and submit for verification.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[2]/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('123456')
        

        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[3]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Clear the email input field, enter the valid registered email 'test@example.com', send verification code again, then input the correct OTP in the OTP field and submit.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[2]/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('')
        

        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[2]/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('test@example.com')
        

        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[3]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input the correct OTP code and click Verify to complete login.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/form/div/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('123456')
        

        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Assert that the user is logged in successfully by checking the presence of user greeting text on the dashboard page.
        user_greeting = await frame.locator('text=Good afternoon, Rajeev').text_content()
        assert user_greeting is not None and 'Good afternoon, Rajeev' in user_greeting, 'User greeting not found, login might have failed.'
        # Assert that the page title is the dashboard title after login.
        page_title = await page.title()
        assert page_title == 'WhatsTask - Project Management', f'Unexpected page title after login: {page_title}'
        # Assert that the navigation links expected on the dashboard are present.
        expected_nav_links = ['Dashboard', 'All Tasks', 'Projects', 'My Tasks', 'Team', 'Analytics', 'Templates', 'AI Admin', 'Deleted Tasks']
        for link_text in expected_nav_links:
            link = await frame.locator(f'text={link_text}').first
            assert await link.is_visible(), f'Navigation link {link_text} not visible on dashboard'
        await asyncio.sleep(5)
    
    finally:
        if context:
            await context.close()
        if browser:
            await browser.close()
        if pw:
            await pw.stop()
            
asyncio.run(run_test())

        if pw:

asyncio.run(run_test())

        assert False, 'Test plan execution failed: generic failure assertion.'
        await asyncio.sleep(5)
    
    finally:
        if context:
            await context.close()
        if browser:
            await browser.close()
        if pw:
            await pw.stop()

import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None

    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:

            except async_api.Error:

        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow

        # Locate and click the delete option/button for the task on the task details page.
        await page.mouse.wheel(0, window.innerHeight)
        

        # Navigate to 'All Tasks' list to check if delete option is available there for the task.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)

        # Check if the delete option is available in the 'Deleted Tasks' section or elsewhere in the UI.

        # Generic failing assertion since expected result is unknown

    finally:

        if browser:

        if pw:
            await pw.stop()

import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Navigate to the template management section by clicking the 'Templates' button in the sidebar or quick actions.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div/div/div/nav/a[7]').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Click the 'Create Template' button to start creating a new task template.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div[3]/main/div/div/div/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Generic failing assertion since expected result is unknown
        assert False, 'Test plan execution failed: generic failure assertion'
        await asyncio.sleep(5)
    
    finally:
        if context:
            await context.close()
        if browser:
            await browser.close()
        if pw:
            await pw.stop()
            
asyncio.run(run_test())

import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Locate and open language settings to change UI language.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

        frame = context.pages[-1]

        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input test email 'test@example.com' into email field.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input invalid verification code to check real-time validation message.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('123')
        

        # Clear the verification code input to test required field validation message.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/form/div/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('')
        

        # Close the verification code input dialog and navigate to a form requiring validation to test validation messages in different languages.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

        frame = context.pages[-1]

        # Navigate to user profile or settings page to locate language selection option.

        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)

            await context.close()

        if pw:
            await pw.stop()

title: TC017-Deep Linking with React Router
description: Verify deep linking to nested routes (e.g., task details inside a project) loads correct content and state.
code:
import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Open a deep link URL for a specific task detail in a new tab to verify correct content and state loading.
        await page.goto('http://localhost:3004/taskdetails?id=59', timeout=10000)
        

        # Perform login using test credentials to verify if deep linking loads correct content and state after authentication.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

    assert await page.locator(f'text={chart_title}').count() > 0
        # Assert the team leaderboard table headers are present

import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Assert all interactive elements are reachable and operable via keyboard
        keyboard_focusable_selectors = ['a', 'button', 'input', 'select', 'textarea', '[tabindex]:not([tabindex="-1"])']
        for selector in keyboard_focusable_selectors:
            elements = await page.query_selector_all(selector)
            for element in elements:
                # Check element is visible and enabled
                is_visible = await element.is_visible()
                is_enabled = await element.is_enabled()
                if is_visible and is_enabled:
                    # Focus element and check if it receives focus
                    await element.focus()
                    focused_element = await page.evaluate('document.activeElement')
                    assert focused_element is not None, f'Element {selector} should receive focus via keyboard'
                    # Optionally, check if element is operable (e.g., clickable)
                    # This can be extended based on element type
        # Assert ARIA roles and labels for interactive elements
        aria_selectors = ['[role]', '[aria-label]', '[aria-labelledby]', '[aria-describedby]']
        for selector in aria_selectors:
            elements = await page.query_selector_all(selector)
            for element in elements:
                # Check that ARIA attributes are not empty
                for attr in ['role', 'aria-label', 'aria-labelledby', 'aria-describedby']:
                    attr_value = await element.get_attribute(attr)
                    if attr_value is not None:
                        assert attr_value.strip() != '', f'ARIA attribute {attr} should not be empty on element {selector}'
        # Assert screen reader announces labels and roles properly
        # This is a complex check, but we can verify that elements with roles have accessible names
        elements_with_roles = await page.query_selector_all('[role]')
        for element in elements_with_roles:
            role = await element.get_attribute('role')
            accessible_name = await element.get_attribute('aria-label') or await element.get_attribute('aria-labelledby')
            assert role is not None and role.strip() != '', 'Element should have a non-empty role attribute'
            assert accessible_name is not None and accessible_name.strip() != '', f'Element with role {role} should have an accessible name via aria-label or aria-labelledby'
        await asyncio.sleep(5)
    
    finally:
        if context:
            await context.close()
        if browser:
            await browser.close()
        if pw:
            await pw.stop()
            
asyncio.run(run_test())

from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():

        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)

        page = await context.new_page()

        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:

                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow

code:
import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Click the 'Show API Test' button to open the API testing interface to simulate network errors.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div[3]/main/div/div[2]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Simulate a transient network error by clicking 'Get Tasks' and intercepting the request to cause a timeout or error.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div[3]/main/div/div[3]/div/div[2]/div[2]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Generic failing assertion since expected result is unknown
        assert False, 'Test failed due to unknown expected result.'
        await asyncio.sleep(5)
    
    finally:
        if context:
            await context.close()
        if browser:
            await browser.close()
        if pw:
            await pw.stop()
            
asyncio.run(run_test())

description: Verify that all system and user errors provide feedback via consistent and accessible alerts and toast notifications.
code:
import asyncio
from playwright import async_api

async def run_test():
    pw = None
    browser = None
    context = None
    
    try:
        # Start a Playwright session in asynchronous mode
        pw = await async_api.async_playwright().start()
        
        # Launch a Chromium browser in headless mode with custom arguments
        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(
            headless=True,
            args=[
                "--window-size=1280,720",         # Set the browser window size
                "--disable-dev-shm-usage",        # Avoid using /dev/shm which can cause issues in containers
                "--ipc=host",                     # Use host-level IPC for better stability
                "--single-process"                # Run the browser in a single process mode
            ],
        )
        
        # Create a new browser context (like an incognito window)
        context = await browser.new_context()
        context.set_default_timeout(5000)
        
        # Open a new page in the browser context
        page = await context.new_page()
        
        # Navigate to your target URL and wait until the network request is committed
        await page.goto("http://localhost:3004", wait_until="commit", timeout=10000)
        
        # Wait for the main page to reach DOMContentLoaded state (optional for stability)
        try:
            await page.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
        except async_api.Error:
            pass
        
        # Iterate through all iframes and wait for them to load as well
        for frame in page.frames:
            try:
                await frame.wait_for_load_state("domcontentloaded", timeout=3000)
            except async_api.Error:
                pass
        
        # Interact with the page elements to simulate user flow
        # Click the Login button to test authentication errors with invalid and valid credentials.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div/div/div/div[2]/div/div/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Trigger authentication error by entering invalid phone number and attempt login to check error feedback.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[2]/form/div[2]/div/div/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('123')
        

        # Switch to Email tab and enter invalid email to trigger authentication error and verify error notification.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div/button[2]').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input invalid email 'invalid-email' and click Send Verification Code to trigger error notification and verify accessibility and dismissability.
        frame = context.pages[-1]

        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('invalid-email')
        

        # Close the login modal and perform a valid login with username 'test' and password 'password' to verify success and absence of error notifications.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Click Login button to open login modal and perform valid login test.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div/div/div/div[2]/div/div/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input valid email 'test@example.com' and click Send Verification Code to proceed with login and verify success and absence of error notifications.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[2]/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('test@example.com')
        

        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/div[3]/form/div[3]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Input an invalid verification code and click Verify to trigger an authentication error notification. Verify the notification appears promptly, is clear, accessible (ARIA roles), and dismissable.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/div[2]/form/div/input').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.fill('000000')
        

        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div[3]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Click 'Show API Test' button to trigger API failure error and verify error notification feedback for promptness, clarity, accessibility, and dismissability.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div[3]/main/div/div[2]/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        # Click 'Test Health Check' button to attempt triggering an API failure error and verify error notification feedback for promptness, clarity, accessibility, and dismissability.
        frame = context.pages[-1]
        elem = frame.locator('xpath=html/body/div/div/div[3]/main/div/div[3]/div/div[2]/div/div/button').nth(0)
        await page.wait_for_timeout(3000); await elem.click(timeout=5000)
        

        assert False, 'Test plan execution failed: generic failure assertion.'
        await asyncio.sleep(5)
    
    finally:
        if context:
            await context.close()
        if browser:
            await browser.close()
        if pw:
            await pw.stop()
            
asyncio.run(run_test())
